.TH INSTALL\-PACKAGES 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
install\-packages.sh \- install packages using platform-specific package managers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B install\-packages.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Installs packages defined in profile and package configuration files using
the appropriate platform-specific package manager. Supports apt, dnf, pacman,
emerge, xbps-install, apk, zypper, pkg, Homebrew, and winget across 18
platforms.
.PP
Packages are resolved from common and platform-specific configuration files
under \fBpackages/\fR, filtered by the active profile.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to use for package selection (e.g., minimal, full, selfhosted).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Print the commands that would be executed without installing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PROFILE
Override the profile name. Equivalent to \fB\-\-profile\fR.
.TP
.B DRY_RUN
Set to \fB1\fR to enable dry-run mode. Equivalent to \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (unsupported platform, missing package manager, failed installation).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install packages for the full profile:
.B install\-packages.sh \-\-profile full
.TP
Preview what would be installed:
.B install\-packages.sh \-\-profile minimal \-\-dry\-run
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
